{"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/accessibility"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["/documentation/accessibility"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Accessibility features help a wide range of people interact with their devices. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many, accessibility is a necessity. For others, it’s a practicality. For example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"closed captions can be necessary for someone who is deaf or hard of hearing, but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also useful for someone watching a video in a noisy environment."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"accessibility-1"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whether you’re developing a new app, or updating an existing one, consider the needs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of all the people who might use your app. People can personalize their devices by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"choosing which accessibility features give them the best user experience.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By designing your app with accessibility in mind, you make it possible for everyone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to enjoy your app. For simplicity, there are four accessibility domains to keep in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"mind when thinking about your users:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Vision — A person may be blind or color blind, or have a vision challenge that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"makes focusing difficult."}],"type":"paragr